#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: data/effects/avfilter/avfilter_compand.xml:5
#, kde-format
msgid "Compress or expand the audio’s dynamic range."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: data/effects/avfilter/avfilter_compand.xml:8
#, fuzzy, kde-format
#| msgid "Audio tracks"
msgid "Attacks"
msgstr "オーディオトラック"

#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: data/effects/avfilter/avfilter_compand.xml:9
#: data/effects/avfilter/avfilter_compand.xml:13
#, kde-format
msgid ""
"A list of times in seconds for each channel over which the instantaneous "
"level of the input signal is averaged to determine its volume. Attacks "
"refers to increase of volume and decays refers to decrease of volume. For "
"most situations, the attack time (response to the audio getting louder) "
"should be shorter than the decay time, because the human ear is more "
"sensitive to sudden loud audio than sudden soft audio. A typical value for "
"attack is 0.3 seconds and a typical value for decay is 0.8 seconds. If "
"specified number of attacks and decays is lower than number of channels, the "
"last set attack/decay will be used for all remaining channels."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: data/effects/avfilter/avfilter_compand.xml:12
#, fuzzy, kde-format
#| msgid "Decay"
msgid "Decays"
msgstr "減衰"

#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: data/effects/avfilter/avfilter_compand.xml:16
#, fuzzy, kde-format
#| msgid "Softness"
msgid "Soft-Knee"
msgstr "柔らかさ"

#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: data/effects/avfilter/avfilter_compand.xml:17
#, kde-format
msgid "Set the curve radius in dB for all joints."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: data/effects/avfilter/avfilter_compand.xml:21
#, kde-format
msgid ""
"Set the additional gain in dB to be applied at all points on the transfer "
"function. This allows for easy adjustment of the overall gain."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: data/effects/avfilter/avfilter_compand.xml:24
#, fuzzy, kde-format
msgid "Initial volume"
msgstr "パン/ズーム"

#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: data/effects/avfilter/avfilter_compand.xml:25
#, kde-format
msgid ""
"Set an initial volume, in dB, to be assumed for each channel when filtering "
"starts. This permits the user to supply a nominal level initially, so that, "
"for example, a very large gain is not applied to initial signal levels "
"before the companding has begun to operate. A typical value for audio which "
"is initially quiet is -90 dB."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: data/effects/avfilter/avfilter_compensationdelay.xml:4
#, fuzzy, kde-format
msgid "Compensation Delay"
msgstr "遷移終了点のサイズ変更"

#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: data/effects/avfilter/avfilter_compensationdelay.xml:8
#, kde-format
msgid ""
"Compensation Delay Line is a metric based delay to compensate differing "
"positions of microphones or speakers.\n"
"For example, you have recorded guitar with two microphones placed in "
"different locations. Because the front of sound wave has fixed speed in "
"normal conditions, the phasing of microphones can vary and depends on their "
"location and interposition. The best sound mix can be achieved when these "
"microphones are in phase (synchronized). Note that a distance of ~30 cm "
"between microphones makes one microphone capture the signal in antiphase to "
"the other microphone. That makes the final mix sound moody. This filter "
"helps to solve phasing problems by adding different delays to each "
"microphone track and make them synchronized.\n"
"\n"
"The best result can be reached when you take one track as base and "
"synchronize other tracks one by one with it. Remember that synchronization/"
"delay tolerance depends on sample rate, too. Higher sample rates will give "
"more tolerance. "
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: data/effects/avfilter/avfilter_compensationdelay.xml:11
#, fuzzy, kde-format
msgid "Millimeter distance"
msgstr "垂直分散"

#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: data/effects/avfilter/avfilter_compensationdelay.xml:12
#, kde-format
msgid ""
"Set millimeters distance. This is compensation distance for fine tuning."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk6 stable6
#: data/effects/avfilter/avfilter_compensationdelay.xml:15
